  "text": "In situ stress measurements were done using a multiple-beam optical stress sensor (MOSS) during deposition of lms (see the schematic in Fig. 1 and ESI S-1 † for more), details of which are mentioned in our previous publication. [CITATION_1] These YSZ lms are cubic (8 mol% or 15 wt%). All the (111) and (100) YSZ lms are of $70 and $400 nm respectively. It is observed that in order to obtain (100) YSZ lms, it is necessary to grow lms thicker than 250 nm. Annealing of these YSZ lms was carried out at 1000 C for one hour in ambient conditions. q-2q scans and uscans of these as-deposited and annealed YSZ lms were done by using a Rigaku Smart lab X-ray diffractometer using Cu-Ka radiation. AFM images of the lms were taken using Bruker Dimension ICON with ScanAsyst2.",
